    • update

      public void update(String name, double x, double y, double z, float pitch, float yaw, net.minecraft.resources.ResourceLocation dimension)
      This Java function updates the location and orientation of a resource with a given name and dimension.
      Parameters:
      name - A string representing the name of the object being updated.
      x - The x-coordinate of the location to be updated.
      y - The parameter "y" represents the vertical position of an object in a three-dimensional space. It is a double data type, which means it can store decimal values.
      z - The z-coordinate of the location being updated.
      pitch - Pitch is the vertical angle of the player's head, measured in degrees. It determines the up and down direction of the player's view. A pitch of 0 means the player is looking straight ahead, while a pitch of 90 means the player is looking straight up.
      yaw - Yaw is a rotation around the vertical axis, measured in degrees. It determines the direction the entity is facing horizontally. A yaw of 0 means the entity is facing south, while a yaw of 90 means the entity is facing west.
      dimension - The dimension parameter is a ResourceLocation object that represents the dimension in which the entity is located. A ResourceLocation is a unique identifier for a resource in Minecraft, and in this case, it is used to identify the dimension by its name. For example, the overworld dimension has the name "minecraft

    • update

      public void update(String name, double x, double y, double z, float pitch, float yaw, net.minecraft.resources.ResourceLocation dimension, @Nullable @Nullable Integer color, @Nullable @Nullable net.minecraft.resources.ResourceLocation icon)
      This function updates the properties of a waypoint object with the given parameters, including name, coordinates, orientation, dimension, color, and icon.
      Parameters:
      name - A string representing the name of the waypoint.
      x - The x-coordinate of the waypoint's location.
      y - The y parameter is a double data type representing the vertical coordinate of the waypoint location.
      z - z is a double variable representing the z-coordinate of a waypoint location in a three-dimensional space.
      pitch - The pitch angle of the waypoint in degrees. It represents the vertical angle of the waypoint from the horizon.
      yaw - The yaw parameter represents the horizontal rotation of the waypoint in degrees. It determines the direction the waypoint is facing.
      dimension - ResourceLocation representing the dimension of the waypoint. A ResourceLocation is a unique identifier for a resource in Minecraft, consisting of a namespace and a path. In this case, it is used to identify the dimension of the waypoint, such as "minecraft:overworld" or "minecraft:nether".
      color - The color of the waypoint in RGB format. If no color is specified, it defaults to white (0xFF_FF_FF).
      icon - The icon parameter is a ResourceLocation object that represents the location of the icon image file for the waypoint. If no icon is specified, it will default to the WaypointIcons.DEFAULT image.
